The paper proposes a new method for subspace clustering, which is a problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper discusses the use of affinity matrices and spectral clustering, which are common techniques in these fields. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of data sets and efficiency, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of correlation and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
